It has a crispy, golden-brown exterior and a soft, gooey center.There are different variations of Kunafa, some use sweet cheese, while others incorporate clotted cream or even a custard-like filling. The syrup is usually flavored with rose or orange blossom water, adding a distinctive aroma.
